The fixes a typo in the pattern matching of array subtype definitions.

The space between "array" and the range should be optional.

t_whatever is array (integer range <>) of t_thing;
vs
t_whatever is array(integer range <>) of t_thing;

- {% extends "base.html" %} -> {% extends "oscar/base.html" %}
- {% extends "layout.html" %} -> {% extends "oscar/layout.html" %}

This allows having independent base.html and layout.html in template root.

Other templates remain untouched, and e.g. creating template dashboard/layout.html will still override oscar/dashboard/layout.html. This might still cause problems if the project has another app named dashboard, for example.

Fixes #1378

